status\", \"from\": 145, \"to\": 155}, {\"ngram\": \"the rising star\", \"from\": 159, \"to\": 174}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 178, \"to\": 187}, {\"ngram\": \"her third gold\", \"from\": 193, \"to\": 207}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 211, \"to\": 226}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky powered to a fourth straight 800m Olympic freestyle title to equal the record for most gold medals won by a woman athlete in any sport.The 17-year-old McIntosh produced a superb late surge to win the 200m individual medley to add to her triumphs in the 400m medley and 200m butterfly.Ledecky has dominated in the 800m since winning the event as a 15-year-old at the London Games in 2012, and while she was pushed all the way by Australian Ariarne Titmus, the defence of her crown never truly looked in danger.The 27-year-old hit the wall in 8min 11.04sec, ahead of Titmus (8:12.29) and the United States' Paige Madden (8:13.00)\\\"I knew Ariarne was going to give me everything she had,\\\" said Ledecky.\", \"from\": 231, \"to\": 937, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 390, \"end\": 398, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.43868477122635e-15, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}, {\"begin\": 667, \"end\": 677, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9994557756966315, \"rank\": 0.0005436133727876812, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 678, \"end\": 692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ariarne Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Ti