f admiration for the American's achievement.\", \"from\": 1844, \"to\": 1954, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1931, \"end\": 1939, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999995215845282, \"rank\": 4.748041003488697e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Unreal'Titmus\", \"from\": 1845, \"to\": 1858}, {\"ngram\": \"Ledecky\", \"from\": 1869, \"to\": 1876}, {\"ngram\": \"the 400m freestyle\", \"from\": 1880, \"to\": 1898}, {\"ngram\": \"admiration\", \"from\": 1912, \"to\": 1922}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She's been winning this race since I was 11 years old and I turn 24 next month.\", \"from\": 1954, \"to\": 2034, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this race\", \"from\": 1974, \"to\": 1983}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That is just remarkable.\", \"from\": 2035, \"to\": 2059, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She's unreal,\\\" she said.McIntosh led from Australian Kaylee McKeown after the backstroke before the USA's Alex Walsh grabbed the advantage at the last turn, following the breaststroke leg.But McIntosh once again produced the killer final lap to grab a thrilling victory.American Kate Douglass took silver while McKeown took the bronze after Walsh, who had finished third, was disqualified.McIntosh was able to enjoy another of her casual strolls around the pool, waving to her fans with a gold medal around her neck.\", \"from\": 2060, \"to\": 2576, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2102, \"end\": 2112, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9994557756966315, \"rank\": 0.0005436133727876812, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 2160, \"end\": 2163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.7277349896184667, \"rank\": 0.3741265067531048, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2166, \"end\": 2176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Walsh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex Walsh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Walsh\"}, {\"begin\": 2252, \"end\": 2260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.43868477122635e-15, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}, {\"begin\": 2339, \"end\": 2352, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kate Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"McIntosh\", \"from\": 2084, \"to\": 2092}, {\"ngram\": \"the backstroke\", \"from\": 2134, \"to\": 2148}, {\"ngram\": \"the advantage\", \"from\": 2185, \"to\": 2198}, {\"ngram\": \"the last turn\", \"from\": 2202, \"to\": 2215}, {\"ngram\": \"the breaststroke leg\", \"from\": 2227, \"to\": 2247}, {\"ngram\": \"the killer final lap\", \"from\": 2281, \"to\": 2301}, {\"ngram\": \"a thrilling victory\", \"from\": 2310, \"to\": 2329}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 2358, \"to\": 2364}, {\"ngram\": \"McKeown\", \"from\": 2371, \"to\": 2378}, {\"ngram\": \"the bronze\", \"from\": 2384, \"to\": 2394}, {\"ngram\": \"Walsh\", \"from\": 2401, \"to\": 2406}, {\"ngram\": \"McIntosh\", \"from\": 2449, \"to\": 2457}, {\"ngram\": \"another\", \"from\": 2476, \"to\": 2483}, {\"ngram\": \"her casual strolls\", \"from\": 2487, \"to\": 2505}, {\"ngram\": \"the pool\", \"from\": 2513, \"to\": 2521}, {\"ngram\": \"her fans\", \"from\": 2533, \"to\": 2541}, {\"ngram\": \"a gold medal\", \"from\": 2547, \"to\": 2559}, {\"ngram\": \"her neck\", \"from\": 2567, \"to\": 2575}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's pretty surreal.\", \"from\": 2576, \"to\": 2597, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am just so proud of myself of how I have been able to recover and manage the events because it is a lot,\\\" said the teenager.Hungary's Kristof Milak claimed his country's second swimming gold of these Games with victory in the men's 100m butterfly.Canada's Josh Liendo took silver while his compatriot Ilya Kharun claimed bronze.It was the second time this week that the Hungarians have been celebrating at La Defense Arena after Hubert Kos took gold in the 200m backstroke.Milak was a silver medallist in the same event in Tokyo and also took silver in the 200m fly behind Leon Marchand this week.He now has two career golds in the fly, adding to his 200m success three years ago.In the mixed 4x100m medley relay, the USA took gold with a world record time to eclipse China and Australia.Their team of Ryan Murphy, Nic Fink, Gretchen Walsh and Torri Huske touched in 3min 37.43sec to narrowly better the mark set by Britain at the Tokyo Games.In the semi-finals of the women's 50m freestyle, Sweden's Sarah Sjoestroem set a new Olympic record with her swim of 23.66, the third-fastest time in history.The Namibian uses AI tools to assist with improved quality, accuracy and efficiency, while maintaining editorial oversight and journalistic integrity.Stay informed with The Namibian - your source for credible journalism.\", \"from\": 2598, \"to\": 3933, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2742, \"end\": 2747, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milak\", \"score\": 0.989